---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Nahj Institute"
  description="Nahj Institute is an independent research centre dedicated to serious scholarship on religion, politics, and society, with a focus on the Muslim world and the Global South."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-inner">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href={`${base}/`}>Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65)">About the Institute</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>An Independent Research Centre for the <em>Muslim World</em> and the Global South</h1>
      <p class="page-hero-sub">
        Dedicated to substantive scholarship on the ideas, societies, and intellectual traditions that the dominant publishing world too often speaks about rather than with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main id="main-content">

    <!-- MISSION -->
    <section class="section-mission" id="mission">
      <div class="mission-layout">
        <div class="mission-label-col">
          <span class="section-label">Our Mission</span>
          <div class="divider-gold"></div>
          <h2>What We Do and Why</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="mission-body">
          <p>
            Nahj Institute is an independent research centre and public forum dedicated to rigorous and formative scholarship on the Muslim world, the Global South, and the ideas that shape them, on their own terms.
          </p>
          <p>
            The dominant publishing infrastructure of the English-speaking world brings genuine expertise to these questions. It also brings frameworks, assumptions, and priorities that are not universal. Scholars, writers, and practitioners whose perspective is shaped by the Muslim world or the Global South often find that their most considered work fits poorly into spaces not built for it.
          </p>
          <p>
            Nahj exists to be one such space. The argument we are making is not that the bar should be lower. It is that the door should be wider.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Islamic intellectual tradition has never been averse to difficulty. Scholars such as Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib, al-Farabi, Ibn Rushd, and Allama Iqbal did not treat received positions as final. They tested them through disciplined reasoning and genuine engagement with the world as they found it. Nahj Institute is grounded in that tradition.
          </p>

          <div class="pullquote">
            <p>"The worth of every person is in what they excel at."</p>
            <cite>Hazrat Ali ibn Abi Talib, Nahj al-Balagha</cite>
          </div>

          <p>
            We are not a seminary, though we take theology seriously. We are not a political organisation, though we engage politics unflinchingly. We are not a media outlet, though we believe ideas must reach people. <strong>We are a place of disciplined inquiry.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ORIGINS -->
    <section class="section-story">
      <div class="story-inner">
        <span class="section-label" style="color:var(--gold)">Our Story</span>
        <div class="divider-gold"></div>
        <h2>How Nahj Institute Came to Be</h2>

        <div class="story-cols">
          <div>
            <p>
              Nahj Institute was founded on a conviction held by a group of scholars, researchers, and practitioners: that the Muslim world and the Global South were being written about extensively, but rarely written from within, at the level of quality and independence that the questions deserve.
            </p>
            <p>
              The name <strong>Nahj</strong> means path, method, or way in Arabic. It evokes Nahj al-Balagha, the collected sermons of Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib: one of the most demanding and profound texts in the Arabic literary canon. The path of knowledge is not a destination but a discipline.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p>
              Scholarship on the Muslim world has often been shaped primarily by frameworks developed within Western academic and policy institutions. These frameworks carry genuine insight, yet they do not always account for the full range of intellectual traditions and social realities of the societies they describe. Nahj Institute supports scholarship that takes those perspectives seriously on their own terms.
            </p>
            <p>
              We remain independent, self-funded, and governed by our founding principles rather than by donors with agendas or states with interests. <strong>That independence is our most valuable asset.</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- VALUES: clean cards, no decorative numbers -->
    <section class="section-values">
      <div class="container">
        <div style="text-align:center">
          <span class="section-label">What We Stand For</span>
          <div class="divider-gold center"></div>
        </div>
        <h2>Our Founding Principles</h2>

        <div class="values-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-num">01</span>
            <h3>Intellectual Rigour</h3>
            <p>Claims require evidence. Arguments require logic. We hold our work to the standards of disciplined scholarship and have no patience for polemic dressed as analysis.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-num">02</span>
            <h3>Moral Courage</h3>
            <p>Some questions are uncomfortable, and some conclusions are unpopular. Nahj will not shy from either. The duty to speak truthfully is an obligation we take with full seriousness.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-num">03</span>
            <h3>Civilisational Rootedness</h3>
            <p>We engage modernity as inheritors of one of history's great intellectual traditions, drawing on classical Islamic thought not as a relic but as a living resource for contemporary questions.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-num">04</span>
            <h3>Genuine Pluralism</h3>
            <p>We welcome contributors across legal schools, political perspectives, and academic disciplines. Disagreement, conducted honestly and respectfully, is among the most productive forces in intellectual life.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="value-card">
            <span class="value-num">05</span>
            <h3>Knowledge in Service</h3>
            <p>Important ideas must reach people, not just specialists. Our scholarship is grounded in genuine concern for the communities we serve, expressed through publication, education, mentorship, and open access, because knowledge that cannot be shared is knowledge half-lived.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHY SERIOUS SCHOLARSHIP MATTERS -->
    <section class="section-writing">
      <div class="writing-inner">
        <div class="writing-label">
          <span class="section-label">Intellectual Culture</span>
          <div class="divider-gold"></div>
          <h2>On the Value of Serious Scholarship</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="writing-body">
          <p>
            Digital communication has expanded access to information while shortening the time given to any one idea. Complex arguments are compressed into commentary, and sustained analysis is displaced by assertion.
          </p>
          <p>
            We believe that essays, research papers, and carefully constructed arguments remain essential for understanding questions that do not yield to simple answers. The Muslim world and the Global South face questions of governance, identity, theology, and international order that deserve thought, not reactions.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our publications and programmes are designed to support that form of intellectual work and to cultivate a readership capable of engaging with it seriously.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FOCUS AREAS -->
    <section class="section-focus" id="focus-areas">
      <div class="focus-header container">
        <span class="section-label">Areas of Inquiry</span>
        <div class="divider-gold"></div>
        <h2>The Questions That Drive Our Work</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="focus-grid container">
        <div class="focus-item">
          <span class="focus-num">01</span>
          <h3>Islamic Thought and Intellectual History</h3>
          <p>Kalam (Islamic speculative theology), ethics, and eschatology: the enduring questions of divine justice, human agency, and the nature of revelation, engaged with classical rigour and contemporary awareness. The history of ideas across the Islamic world, from Baghdad to Cordoba to Lucknow, and the living relevance of that inheritance today.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-item">
          <span class="focus-num">02</span>
          <h3>Politics, Governance, and Global Affairs</h3>
          <p>Islamic political theory and the question of legitimacy in Muslim-majority states. Democracy, constitutionalism, and the relationship between religion and public life. The Muslim world in the global order, from the Gulf to South Asia, from the Sahel to Southeast Asia, with strategic analysis grounded in historical depth and ethical seriousness.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-item">
          <span class="focus-num">03</span>
          <h3>Society, Identity, and Culture</h3>
          <p>Family, identity, gender, generational change, and the pressures bearing on Muslim communities in the modern world. Literature, the arts, and material culture are intellectual sources rather than ornaments. The Muslim world is examined with rigour rather than reactivity, and with literary seriousness rather than sociological distance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-item">
          <span class="focus-num">04</span>
          <h3>Coexistence and Interfaith Thought</h3>
          <p>The theory and practice of living well with difference. Comparative theology, the ethics of dialogue, sectarian conflict, and the intellectual traditions within Islam and across religions have resources for these questions. We approach this area not as a diplomatic exercise but as a serious field of inquiry.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-item">
          <span class="focus-num">05</span>
          <h3>Science, Ethics, and the Human Condition</h3>
          <p>Bioethics, artificial intelligence, environmental thought, and the enduring question of what it means to be human are examined with the resources of Islamic intellectual tradition and in dialogue with contemporary scientific thought. The questions raised by new technologies and the ecological crisis do not respect the boundary between the secular and the sacred.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- TEAM TEASER -->
    <section class="section-team-teaser">
      <div class="team-inner">
        <div class="team-text">
          <span class="section-label">The People</span>
          <div class="divider-gold"></div>
          <h2>Leadership and Core Team</h2>
          <p>
            Nahj Institute is led and staffed by an international network of scholars, researchers, and practitioners with expertise across Islamic intellectual history, political theory, philosophy, and the social sciences.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a href={`${base}/team`} class="btn-team">Meet Our Team →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- VISITOR GUIDE -->
    <section class="section-guide">
      <div class="guide-inner">
        <span class="section-label" style="color:var(--gold)">Visitor Guide</span>
        <div class="divider-gold"></div>
        <h2>New Here? Here Is How to Engage with Nahj Institute</h2>

        <div class="guide-steps">
          <div class="guide-step">
            <span class="step-num">Step 01</span>
            <h3>Read Our Research</h3>
            <p>Start with our featured essays and policy papers, written to be substantive and worth your time whether you are a specialist or an engaged general reader.</p>
            <a href={`${base}/research`}>Browse the Archive →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-step">
            <span class="step-num">Step 02</span>
            <h3>Attend an Event</h3>
            <p>Our lecture series and seminars bring distinguished thinkers into direct conversation. Many events are free and open to all, with recordings available online.</p>
            <a href={`${base}/events`}>View Upcoming Events →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-step">
            <span class="step-num">Step 03</span>
            <h3>Enter a Competition</h3>
            <p>Our annual writing competitions are open to students and emerging writers. Generous prizes, rigorous feedback, and real publication opportunities.</p>
            <a href={`${base}/community#competitions`}>Competition Details →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-step">
            <span class="step-num">Step 04</span>
            <h3>Join a Programme</h3>
            <p>From writing workshops and research bootcamps to one-on-one mentorship and career counselling, our student programmes accelerate serious intellectual formation.</p>
            <a href={`${base}/community#student`}>Student Programmes →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-step">
            <span class="step-num">Step 05</span>
            <h3>Contribute Your Writing</h3>
            <p>We accept submissions from researchers, academics, and informed practitioners. Our editorial standards are high but we actively look for new voices.</p>
            <a href={`${base}/research/submit`}>Submission Guidelines →</a>
          </div>
          <div class="guide-step">
            <span class="step-num">Step 06</span>
            <h3>Support the Institute</h3>
            <p>Nahj operates independently, without state or corporate patronage. If our work matters to you, consider supporting it financially or by sharing what we produce.</p>
            <a href={`${base}/contact`}>How to Support Us →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section-cta">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="inst-strip">
          <div class="inst-item">
            <strong>01 — Independent</strong>
            <p>Not affiliated with any state, political party, or commercial interest. Our editorial and research decisions are governed by our founding principles alone. That independence is what makes our voice worth anything.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inst-item">
            <strong>02 — International</strong>
            <p>Contributors and researchers based across the Muslim world, South Asia, Africa, the Middle East, and diaspora communities globally. The questions we address do not belong to one country or one tradition, and neither do the voices we publish.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inst-item">
            <strong>03 — Open Access</strong>
            <p>All research and essays published freely, for academic and general readership alike. Knowledge that cannot be reached cannot do its work. There are no paywalls and no subscriptions.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inst-item">
            <strong>04 — Interdisciplinary</strong>
            <p>Drawing on theology, political theory, philosophy, history, literature, and the social sciences. The questions that matter most resist the boundaries that disciplines impose on them.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="inst-item">
            <strong>05 — From Within</strong>
            <p>The Muslim world and the Global South have long been subjects of study. Nahj exists to ensure they are also sites of inquiry: places from which knowledge is produced, not only about which knowledge is produced.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cta-center">
          <span class="section-label">Get in Touch</span>
          <div class="divider-gold center"></div>
          <h2>We Would Like to Hear from You</h2>
          <p>Whether you have a research proposal, a question about our programmes, a partnership idea, or simply something worth discussing, our door is open.</p>
          <div>
            <a href={`${base}/contact`} class="btn-primary" style="margin-right: 0.75rem;">Contact the Institute</a>
            <a href={`${base}/research`} class="btn-outline-light">Read Our Research</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <style>
  /* ── MISSION ────────────────────────────────────── */
  .section-mission { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--cream); }

  .mission-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2.2fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .mission-label-col { padding-top: 0.25rem; position: sticky; top: 4.5rem; }

  .mission-label-col h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .mission-body p {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    line-height: 1.78;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .mission-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .mission-body strong { font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy); }

  /* Pull quote */
  .pullquote {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
    padding: 0.75rem 0 0.75rem 1.75rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  .pullquote p {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--navy);
    line-height: 1.45;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .pullquote cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-style: normal;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* ── STORY (dark section) ───────────────────────── */
  .section-story {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .section-story::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 80% at 90% 50%, rgba(27,94,111,0.25) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .story-inner { max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1; }

  .story-inner h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    line-height: 1.18;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .story-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
  }
  .story-cols p {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72);
    line-height: 1.78;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 1.4rem;
  }
  .story-cols p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .story-cols strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.92); font-weight: 500; }

  /* VALUES: clean grid, NO decorative numbers */
  .section-values { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--cream-dark); }

  .section-values h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2px;
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .value-card {
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 2rem 1.75rem;
    border-top: 3px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.25s;
  }
  .value-card:hover { border-color: var(--gold); }

  .value-num {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--gold);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .value-card h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.6rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
  }

  .value-card p {
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.78;
  }

  /* ── WRITING / INTELLECTUAL CULTURE ─────────────── */
  .section-writing { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--cream); border-top: 1px solid var(--cream-dark); }
  .writing-inner {
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2.2fr;
    gap: 5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .writing-label h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    line-height: 1.12;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    position: sticky;
    top: 4.5rem;
  }
  .writing-body p {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    line-height: 1.78;
    font-weight: 300;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .writing-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ── FOCUS AREAS ────────────────────────────────── */
  .section-focus { padding: 5rem 2rem; background: var(--cream-dark); }
  .focus-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .focus-header h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .focus-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 0;
  }
  .focus-item {
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--cream);
    background: var(--white);
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .focus-item:hover { background: var(--cream); }
  .focus-num {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--gold);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .focus-item h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .focus-item p {
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  /* ── TEAM TEASER ────────────────────────────────── */
  .section-team-teaser {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
  }
  .team-inner {
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 3rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .team-text h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .team-text p { font-size: 20px; color: var(--muted); max-width: 580px; line-height: 1.80; font-weight: 300; }

  .btn-team {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--navy);
    color: var(--navy);
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.88rem 2rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: background 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }
  .btn-team:hover { background: var(--navy); color: var(--gold); }

  /* ── VISITOR GUIDE ──────────────────────────────── */
  .section-guide {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .section-guide::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 70% at 80% 40%, rgba(200,162,82,0.07) 0%, transparent 70%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .guide-inner { max-width: 1120px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .guide-inner h2 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--white);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    line-height: 1.18;
  }
  .guide-steps {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }
  .guide-step { padding: 2rem 1.75rem; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07); }
  .guide-step:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); }
  .step-num { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); display: block; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .guide-step h3 { font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .guide-step p { font-size: 19px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.60); line-height: 1.78; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .guide-step a { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.2s; }
  .guide-step a:hover { color: var(--gold-light); }

  /* ── CTA ────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .section-cta { background: var(--navy); padding: 5rem 2rem; }

  /* Institutional profile strip */
  .inst-strip {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }
  .inst-item {
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    border-right: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  .inst-item:last-child { border-right: none; }
  .inst-item:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); }
  .inst-item strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
